[30;1m279 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m280 | [0m[35m    The PLP method analyzes the onset strength envelope in the frequency domain[0m
[30;1m281 | [0m[35m    to find a locally stable tempo for each frame.  These local periodicities[0m
[30;1m282 | [0m[35m    are used to synthesize local half-waves, which are combined such that peaks[0m
[30;1m283 | [0m[35m    coincide with rhythmically salient frames (e.g. onset events on a musical time grid).[0m
[30;1m284 | [0m[35m    The local maxima of the pulse curve can be taken as estimated beat positions.[0m

[30;1m547 | [0m[35m    """Compute roll-off frequency.[0m
[30;1m548 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m549 | [0m[35m    The roll-off frequency is defined for each frame as the center frequency[0m
[30;1m550 | [0m[35m    for a spectrogram bin such that at least roll_percent (0.85 by default)[0m
[30;1m551 | [0m[35m    of the energy of the spectrum in this frame is contained in this bin and[0m
[30;1m552 | [0m[35m    the bins below. This can be used to, e.g., approximate the maximum (or[0m
[30;1m553 | [0m[35m    minimum) frequency by setting roll_percent to a value close to 1 (or 0).[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m315[0m[34m of [0m[33m761[0m[31m ]--[0m

[30;1m513 | [0m[35m        if k < n_bands:[0m
[30;1m514 | [0m[35m            sub_band = sub_band[..., :-1, :][0m
[30;1m515 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m516 | [0m[35m        # Always take at least one bin from each side[0m
[30;1m517 | [0m[35m        idx = np.rint(quantile * np.sum(current_band))[0m

[30;1m105 | [0m[35m        - If `True`, the signal ``y`` is padded so that frame[0m
[30;1m106 | [0m[35m          `t` is centered at ``y[t * hop_length]``.[0m
[30;1m107 | [0m[35m        - If `False`, then frame ``t`` begins at ``y[t * hop_length]``[0m
[30;1m108 | [0m[35m    pad_mode : string[0m
[30;1m109 | [0m[35m        If ``center=True``, the padding mode to use at the edges of the signal.[0m

[30;1m114 | [0m[35m        Smaller values improve the temporal resolution of the STFT (i.e. the[0m
[30;1m115 | [0m[35m        ability to discriminate impulses that are closely spaced in time)[0m
[30;1m116 | [0m[35m        at the expense of frequency resolution (i.e. the ability to discriminate[0m
[30;1m117 | [0m[35m        pure tones that are closely spaced in frequency). This effect is known[0m
